com.solidfire.element.api

Class FibreChannelPortInfo

  • Object
    • FibreChannelPortInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class FibreChannelPortInfo
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Fibre Channel Node Port Info object returns information about all Fibre Channel ports on a node, or for one node in the cluster. The same information is returned for all ports or port information for one node. This information is returned with the API method ListNodeFibreChannelPortInfo (in the SolidFire API Guide).
    See Also:

public FibreChannelPortInfo(String firmware,

                          String serial,

                          String state,
                          String switchWwn,
                          String wwnn,
                          String wwpn)
        Fibre Channel Node Port Info object returns information about all Fibre Channel ports on a node, or for one node in the cluster. The same information is returned for all ports or port information for one node. This information is returned with the API method ListNodeFibreChannelPortInfo (in the SolidFire API Guide).
        Parameters:
        firmware - [required] The version of the firmware installed on the Fibre Channel port.
        hbaPort - [required] The ID of the individual HBA port.
        model - [required] Model of the HBA on the port.
        nPortID - [required] Unique SolidFire port node ID.
        pciSlot - [required] Slot in which the pci card resides on the Fibre Channel node hardware.
        serial - [required] Serial number on the Fibre Channel port.
        speed - [required] Speed of the HBA on the port.
        state - [required] Possible values:
        switchWwn - [required] The World Wide Name of the Fibre Channel switch port.
        wwnn - [required] World Wide Node Name of the HBA node.
        wwpn - [required] World Wide Port Name assigned to the physical port of the HBA.
        Since:
        7.0
